'''Saeed Hallafi''' (According to [[Asian Football Confederation|AFC]] '''Saeed Khalafi''')<ref>http://www.the-afc.com/uploads/Documents/competitions/fixtures/2528.pdf</ref> ({{lang-fa| <U+0633><U+0639><U+06CC><U+062F> <U+062D><U+0644><U+0627><U+0641><U+06CC> }}, born 20 May 1990 in [[Ahvaz]])<ref name="pe">http://fc-perspolis.com/532/<U+0645><U+0635><U+0627><U+062D><U+0628><U+0647>_<U+0627><U+062E><U+062A><U+0635><U+0627><U+0635><U+06CC>_<U+0628><U+0627>_<U+0633><U+0639><U+06CC><U+062F>_<U+062D><U+0644><U+0627><U+0641><U+06CC>/#More</ref> is an [[Iran]]ian [[Association football|footballer]] who currently plays as [[Winger (sports)|Winger]] for [[Machine Sazi Tabriz F.C.|Machine Sazi]] in the [[Azadegan League]].<ref name="pe"/>

==Club career==
He started his professional career in [[Sanat Naft F.C.|Sanat Naft]] and moved to [[PAS Hamedan F.C.|Pas]] but did not play any match. He moved back to [[Sanat Naft F.C.|Sanat Naft]] for the next season in First Division.<ref name="pe"/> He moved to [[Rah Ahan F.C.|Rah Ahan]] in June 2009.

